criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Aged 18 to 80 years old;

          2. Symptomatic sinus bradycardia;

          3. Not meet the class I indications for pacemaker implantation.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Structural heart disease, heart surgery history;

          2. Drug-induced SB, sinus pause >2.0 s, positive atropine test, corrected sinus node
             recovery time (cSNRT) >525 ms;

          3. Any atrial or ventricular arrhythmia, or a history of ablation procedures to treat
             atrial tachyarrhythmias;

          4. With Significant congenital heart disease, ejection fraction was <40% measured by
             echocardiography;

          5. Allergic to contrast media;

          6. Contraindication to anticoagulation medications;

          7. Severe pulmonary disease e.g. restrictive pulmonary disease, chronic obstructive
             disease (COPD);

        9. Poor general health; 10.Life expectancy less than 6 months.
